@node install "Installing the program"

This program does not need any assigns, environment variables etc.
So you can try it without installing it. If you want to install it:
Double click on the icon "install-activity" and answer the questions.
@endnode

@node gui "How to use Activity"
When you start the program, a window will appear on your workbench screen,
if you want it. You cannot start it more than once. When you start it a
second time, the interface is opened. Always, even if you have CX_POPUP=NO.
Other commodities do this too!
Unless you use @{"FORMAT" link args}, the title reads:

  L(eft button):a R(ight button):b K(eyboard):c

For the keyboard, qualifiers (for example shift) do not count.
I don't add lame helptexts on the menus.

You can press some keys in the window:

* ESC, Q, H - Hide window
* X - Exit  the program
* R - Reset counters to zero and save them
* A - Show "about" requester
* S - Save window position (if started from WB) and counters
* Help - Show "help" requester
@endnode

@node args "Tool types / cli args"

* CX_PRIORITY=number - priority - who gets first the InputEvent? MagicMenu
    users should set this one higher than MagicMenu's CX_PRIORITY or clicks of
    the right mousebutton will not be counted if it was for menus.
* CX_POPUP=YES or NO - should the window open at startup?
* CX_POPKEY=hotkey description - key to pop up window
    (Workbench only, default is control alt m)
* X=number - x-coordinate of window
* Y=number - y-coordinate of window
* FORMAT=string - Title of window.
    The following format codes are supported:
      - %L - left mouse button
      - %I - middle mouse button
      - %R - right mouse button
      - %M - mouse move (not updated because it takes far too much CPU time)
      - %K - keyboard
      - %% - % sign
    Default: L:%L R:%R K:%K
* FILE=filename - file for counters (Default: no file)
* SAVETIME=number - Auto-save time, in seconds. (Default: no auto-save)
    The auto-save only saves the counters. All save-commands save the
    counters and the settings (currently only position of window).
* QUITKEY=hotkey description - key to save counters and exit the program.
    This is for safety. If you save on harddisk, you should press this key
    just before you reboot. Otherwise it may corrupt your harddisk
    (rebooting while writing). The default is control lcommand m.
* WIDTH=width of window in pixels - Do not make too small! The program does not
    check it. (Default: 300)
@endnode

@node arexx "ARexx port"

Activity has an ARexx port. It is named: ACTIVITY. The commands are listed
below:
  *** CX commands
  * APPEAR, SHOW: show interface. Returns 10 on failure.
  * DISAPPEAR, HIDE: hide interface
  * DISABLE: stop the counting of inputevents and the hotkeys of Activity.
  * ENABLE: enable again. It does not nest.
  * KILL, QUIT: Quit Activity
  *** Other commands
  * SAVE: save counters
  * GET: Get something. Possible arguments:
    * X, LEFTE: leftedge
    * Y, TO: topedge
    * W: width
    * L: left button clicks
    * R: right button clicks
    * MI, I: middle button clicks
    * M: mouse move
    * K: keyboard
    * FO, FM: title format
    * T: window title. Also possible when the window is not opened.
    * F: filename for the counters. Fails with RC=10 when it was not specified
          at startup.
    * V: version string
    * O: window open? TRUE=yes, FALSE=no
    These commands do the same: GetV, GetVersion, Get V, Get Version.
      (Rexx makes it uppercase and Activity removes spaces and
      ignores everything after the letters listed above)
  * ASTATS: start @{"AStats" link astats}. This command is asynchonous, i.e. it returns after
      AStats has been started.
  * RESET: reset counters and save them.
  * FORMAT: format left, right, move, key and mid values (in that order)
      according to the preferences of the user.

Demo script:
@{"view" link Demo.arx/main}
@{"run" system "rx <>CON:////Demo.arx/close/wait Demo.arx"} (Activity must be running)
@endnode

@node astats "AStats program"

AStats is a simple program to show Activity STATisticS. It draws graphs of
the five counters of Activity. It uses the save file of Activity. Give the
filename as an argument. Another way is the @{"ASTATS" link arexx} arexx
command or the Extras/AStats menu option of Activity. In that case you don't
have to type in the filename.
When you run AStats and Activity simultanaously,
you can get a requester "Couldn't save counters". This happens when Activity
wants to save the counters, but AStats has the file open. When this happens,
press "Retry" when AStats is done.
@endnode

@node history "History"

V2.2 03-May-1996
  * No problems anymore with large screen-text fonts (but it is possible a
      requester does not fit on the screen. If this happens, set the screen
      font to Topaz 8. The requesters fit on a 640x200 Topaz 8 screen.)
  * Activity's window now opens on default public screen
  * Change tooltypes in Installer script
  * Middle mouse button support (I am not able to test it, so please contact
    me if it does not work)
  * New menu option "Extras/AStats" to run AStats
  * AStats' window now has a sizegadget
  * Added an @{"AREXX port" link arexx}
  * Fixed Enforcer hit while writing tooltypes
  * When you type a wrong key in @{"AStats'" link astats} window, you will see an help text now.
      (Before: empty window and sometimes Enforcer hits)
V2.1 07-Mar-1996
  * Fixed bug causing $0100000C alerts when saving tooltypes when the number
      of tooltypes was odd
  * NewLookMenus for 3.0+ users
  * Window width customizable
  * Window is now activated when opened.
  * The screen the window is on is put to front.
V2.0 26-Jan-1996
  * Added save
  * Now uses less CPU time when window is hidden
  * Removed mouse-move updating: it took too much CPU time
  * Added a very simple statistics program
  * About and help requesters now open on the screen the window is on, not
      on the default public screen
  * More configurable: window title, window position
V1.0 31-Dec-1995
  Initial release
@endnode

